      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction: Dec 29, 2006, article about changes in medical practice misstated reason for using sandbags to stabilize heads of patients undergoing cataract surgert</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Science Times on Dec. 29 about changes in medical practice over the past 50 years misstated the reason that sandbags were once used to stabilize the heads of patients undergoing cataract surgery. Sandbags were used partly because of problems with suturing, not to protect newly implanted lenses. This correction was delayed for research.</p>
      </block>
